.TH "copy_oldmem_page" 9 "copy_oldmem_page" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
copy_oldmem_page \- copy one page from old kernel memory
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" copy_oldmem_page
.BI "(unsigned long pfn "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ","
.BI "size_t csize "  ","
.BI "unsigned long offset "  ","
.BI "int userbuf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pfn" 12
page frame number to be copied
.IP "buf" 12
buffer where the copied page is placed
.IP "csize" 12
number of bytes to copy
.IP "offset" 12
offset in bytes into the page
.IP "userbuf" 12
if set, \fIbuf\fP is in a user address space
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function copies one page from old kernel memory into buffer pointed by
\fIbuf\fP. If \fIbuf\fP is in userspace, set \fIuserbuf\fP to 1. Returns number of bytes
copied or negative error in case of failure.
